[[File:Force_Stealth.jpg|thumb|A [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-user]] under the guise of Force stealth.]]
{{Quote|You blend in with the universe. Think of it as Force camouflage. The trick is to become so comfortable with it that you can slip into this state of being&hellip; dissolved, yet still carry on functioning, fully aware.|[[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]]|<ref name="Sacrifice">''[[Legacy of the Force: Sacrifice]]''</ref>}}
'''Force stealth''', also referred to as '''Force Concealment''' or '''Buried Presence''',<ref name="TFUCG">''[[The Force Unleashed Campaign Guide]]''</ref> was a [[Force power/Legends|power]] that was used by highly skilled [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitives]] to mask their [[The Force/Legends|Force]] alignment ([[Light side of the Force/Legends|Light]] or [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|Dark]]), their ability to use the Force, or even their entire presence from other Force-sensitives.

==Effects==
This ability manifested in different forms; [[Vergere]] would [[Art of the Small|shrink her presence]] in [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] to a microscopic size, where she was almost undetectable and able to avoid mental attacks, even from [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]]. [[Palpatine/Legends|Darth Sidious]] was the most powerful and notorious user of this power, having hid his dark nature for over three [[Standard decade/Legends|decades]] from the [[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi High Council]], even when in the same room. It has been argued that [[Revan/Legends|Revan]] may have used the technique to shield his true [[Light side of the Force/Legends|light side]] affiliation on [[Korriban/Legends|Korriban]] in order to [[Skirmish on Korriban|infiltrate]] the [[Sith Academy (Korriban)|Sith Academy]]. [[Kreia|Darth Traya]] used a powerful version of this to evade both the surviving [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] and her [[Sith apprentice/Legends|Sith apprentices]], as well as mask her nature from her own student, [[Meetra Surik]] who in turn may have mastered this ability.<ref name="KOTOR II">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic II: The Sith Lords]]''</ref> Other users included the [[Jensaarai/Legends|Jensaarai]], who constantly hid their presence in the Force from both the Sith under [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] and the [[New Jedi Order]].

[[Xanatos]] used this kind of power to shield his presence when he [[Incident at the Jedi Temple|infiltrated]] the [[Jedi Temple/Legends|Jedi Temple]]. He later taught it to the corrupted [[Jedi Initiate/Legends|Jedi Initiate]] [[Bruck Chun]].<ref name="Captive Temple">''[[Jedi Apprentice: The Captive Temple]]''</ref>

[[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Masters]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and [[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]] both used a form of Force concealment to shield themselves from [[Darth/Legends|Darths]] Sidious and Vader in their [[Exile (punishment)/Legends|exile]].

One of the more prevalent derivatives of Force Concealment was the '''Quey'tek''' [[Meditation/Legends|meditation]]. When properly applied and maintained, a [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] or [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] could mask their own dark signatures appearing completely benevolent to even the most powerful and alert Jedi.<ref name="Cestus Deception">''[[The Cestus Deception]]''</ref> Known users of the Quey'tek meditation included [[Asajj Ventress/Legends|Asajj Ventress]],<ref name="Cestus Deception" /> [[Dooku/Legends|Darth Tyranus]] (although Obi-Wan Kenobi and Anakin Skywalker were eventually able to see through his shielding),<ref name="Labyrinth of Evil">''[[Labyrinth of Evil]]''</ref> [[Darth Maul/Legends|Darth Maul]],<ref name="Shadow Hunter">''[[Darth Maul: Shadow Hunter]]''</ref> and possibly [[Darth Zannah/Legends|Darth Zannah]].

Anakin's grandson, [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo]], also used this technique to hide [[Lumiya]]'s dark presence. Jacen also used it to hide his own emotions from other Force-users whenever he was upset or under stress.<ref name="Tempest">''[[Legacy of the Force: Tempest]]''</ref> [[Ben Skywalker]] later gained this power from Jacen and likewise his mother, [[Mara Jade Skywalker]], learned it from him.<ref name="Sacrifice" /> Luke Skywalker used this ability to bypass [[Gethzerion]] and other [[Nightsisters/Legends|Nightsisters]] while infiltrating the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] [[Dathomir Imperial Prison|prison]] on [[Dathomir/Legends|Dathomir]], even taught it to [[Teneniel Djo]];<ref name="Courtship">''[[The Courtship of Princess Leia]]''</ref> he would later employ it to sneak up on Jacen during the [[Battle of Kashyyyk (Second Galactic Civil War)|Battle of Kashyyyk]].<ref name="Inferno">''[[Legacy of the Force: Inferno]]''</ref> Luke's control of this Force ability was so precise he was able to allow certain individuals including his own son to sense his presence when hiding from adversaries. By the time Jacen became Darth Caedus, he had used the power so much that he was able to constantly remain hidden with little effort, and taught the power to his apprentice, [[Tahiri Veila]].

The [[Hidden Ones]] of the [[Baran Do]] sages used this power to fake their own [[Death/Legends|deaths]] during their [[Dying ceremony|farewell ceremony]].<ref name="Outcast">''[[Fate of the Jedi: Outcast]]''</ref> The [[Agents of Ossus]] were adept at using this power to evade the [[Inquisitorius/Legends|Inquisitorius]] and other Imperial Force-hunters during the Dark Times.<ref name="TFUCG" />

==Behind the scenes==
In the [[Wizards of the Coast]] ''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game]]'', this ability is referred to as "Force Stealth". The original version allowed a Force-user to not only hide their Force sensitivity but to increase their ability to hide. The [[Star Wars Roleplaying Game Revised Core Rulebook|Revised version]] only provides a way to cloak one's connection to the Force, and any use of the Force causes this ability to fail, although [[Jedi Sentinel/Legends|Jedi Sentinels]] can learn to use Force Stealth and Force Camouflage together. The [[Star Wars Roleplaying Game Saga Edition Core Rulebook|''Saga Edition'']] splits the ability into a number of distinct powers and talents.

